                "ability_type_abbrev": "Ex"
            },
            {
                "type": "stat_block_section",
                "subtype": "special_ability",
                "text": "Once every 1d4 rounds as a standard action, a mature solar wisp can hurl a portion of its burning form at a grid intersection within 120 feet, at which point the flames detonate, dealing 10d6 fire damage to all creatures within a 20-foot-radius burst. An affected creature can attempt a DC 24 Reflex saving throw to halve the damage.",
